As kinsmen appeal to President to retain him

As ther lobby for ministerial and other federal appointments intensify within the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), the Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, may have deployed his kinsmen in Kwara State to beg President Muhammadu Buhari for his re-appointment in the next federal cabinet.
Apparently, the All Progressives Congress (APC) consultative forum in Irepodun Local Government Area, Kwara State, appealed to President Muhammadu Buhari to retain the Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, when appointing new ministers for the next cabinet in his second term.
ALSO READ: What brought Tinubu to Aso Rock?
The APC Consultative Forum from Irepodun Local Government Area, Kwara State, is construed as the lobby team of the Information and Culture Minister, Lai Mohammed, who is the current representative of Kwara State in the federal cabinet.
National Daily learned that the Forum led by Hezekiah Oyedepo explained that Lai Mohammed has been outstanding and has justified the confidence reposed in him in various appointments offered him in the APC and the federal government, thereby, making a case for his re-appointment in the next Federal Executive Council (FEC) in the second term of President Buhari.
National Daily further learned that the Oyedepo-led APC Consultative Forum listed the achievements of Lai Mohammed, on the basis of which they begged the president and APC leadership to ensure that Lai Mohammed is not replaced with another APC leader in Kwara State.

			
